@startuml seq-open-file
'' ============================================================================
'' vinary-viewer — Sequence: launch `vv README.md` → first paint (full round trip)
''
'' PlantUML over Mermaid because: this flow spans two OS processes plus the
'' preload seam, needs activation bars to show where the watcher stays live after
'' the call returns, and `== phase ==` dividers to separate boot / content / tree.
'' PlantUML sequence diagrams give all three with `autonumber`; Mermaid omits the
'' divider concept and renders weaker lifelines.
'' ============================================================================
!include _vv-theme.iuml

title Open a file — `vv README.md` → first render

autonumber "0:"

actor User #white
participant "main.core" as Core MAIN_COLOR
participant "main.service" as Svc MAIN_COLOR
participant "Filesystem\n+ chokidar" as FS FS_COLOR
participant "preload `window.vv`" as Vv IPC_COLOR
participant "renderer.core\n`bridge!`" as RCore RENDERER_COLOR
participant "re-frame\nevents/fx" as RF REFRAME_COLOR
participant "DataScript\nconn" as DS DATASCRIPT_COLOR
participant "unified\npipeline" as MD MARKDOWN_COLOR
participant "reagent UI" as UI RENDERER_COLOR

== boot ==
User -> Core : `vv README.md`
activate Core
Core -> Core : `create-window!`\n(contextIsolation, preload)
Core -> Svc : `service/init!`\n(register ipcMain)
Core -> Core : `loadFile index.html`
RCore -> RCore : `init`: dispatch-sync `[:db/init]`,\n`install-bridge!`, `bridge!`, `mount!`
Core -> Svc : on **did-finish-load**:\n`service/open! wc "README.md"`
deactivate Core
activate Svc

== content ==
Svc -> FS : `readFileSync` (utf8)
FS --> Svc : text
Svc -> Vv : `webContents.send`\n**vv:content** {path, kind:"markdown", text}
Vv -> RCore : `onContent` cb
RCore -> RF : dispatch `[:content/received …]`
activate RF
RF -> DS : `:ds/transact`\n{:doc/path :doc/kind :doc/text :doc/stamp}
RF -> MD : `:markdown/render {text path on-done}`
deactivate RF
activate MD
MD --> RF : Promise resolves -> dispatch\n`[:content/rendered path stamp result]`
deactivate MD
activate RF
RF -> DS : `:ds/transact`\n{:doc/html :doc/toc :doc/assets}
deactivate RF
DS -> RF : `d/listen!` → `[:ds/changed]`\n(`:ds/rev` ++)
RF -> UI : `:tabs` / `:doc/active` recompute
UI -> UI : `content-view` → `markdown-body`\n`set! innerHTML html`

== tree ==
Svc -> Svc : `repo-tree` (`git rev-parse` + `ls-files`)
Svc -> Vv : `webContents.send`\n**vv:tree** {root, files}
Vv -> RF : `onTree` → `[:tree/received]`
RF -> UI : `:ui/tree` → `file-tree` renders

== watch (stays live) ==
Svc -> FS : `chokidar.watch path`\n(ignoreInitial, awaitWriteFinish)
note over Svc, FS
  The watcher persists after `open!` returns.
  Every later `change` / `add` re-runs the
  **content** phase (see seq-live-refresh).
end note
deactivate Svc

legend right
  |= Colour |= Concept |
  | <#3A5BA0> | MAIN / Node IO |
  | <#2D9574> | Renderer / UI |
  | <#B1951D> | IPC seam |
  | <#A45BAD> | DataScript content cache |
  | <#4F97D7> | re-frame |
  | <#67B11D> | markdown pipeline |
  | <#9F8766> | filesystem / chokidar |
endlegend
@enduml
